Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic properties of caesium magnesium monophosphate
Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity measurements of the crystalline phosphate CsMgPO4 of a tridymite structure were performed between T = (7 and 650) K. The thermodynamic functions were calculated and the fractal dimension Dfr evaluated. From the solution reaction calorimetry, the standard enthalpy of CsMgPO4 formation at T = 298.15 K was found. Thermochemical parameters of formation and were determined by combining the data obtained by these techniques
